Conclusions
Rates of hospital admission for ACSCs are increasingly used as a measure of the effectiveness of primary care. However, different conceptual interpretations of the term ‘ACSC’ and use of differing definitions and diagnostic codes impact on the proportion of admissions that are attributed as ACSCs. Some resolution of these inconsistencies is required for this measure to be more useful to decision makers.},
